OL,3,COver 900 classroom assistants working
OL,4,Cwithout access check
OL,6,FIn response to a question Education
OL,7,FMinister Paul Givan said: "While all
OL,8,Fclassroom assistants are required to
OL,9,Fcomplete an Access NI check, in the
OL,10,Fcase of a short-term temporary hire or
OL,11,Femergency cover it's not always
OL,12,Fpossible to finalise the check prior
OL,13,Fto engagement.
OL,15,F"In such situations, the school
OL,16,Fprincipal is required to complete a
OL,17,Frisk assessment and take all necessary
OL,18,Fsteps to ensure the safeguarding of
OL,19,Fchildren and young people.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/4
